ary":"Lady Agnes Shaw於大約1425年出生在英國。她於1445年之前與Sir Henry Lockwood在英國結婚。他們至少是1個女兒的父母。"},"zh-hans":{"about 1425–":"大约1425年–殁","1425–Male":"1425年–殁","1445–1510":"1445年–1510年","1425–Female":"1425年–殁","1425":"1425年","before 1445":"1445年之前","1445":"1445年","1455":"1455年","1510":"1510年","about 1425":"大约1425年","about 1445":"大约1445年","England":"英国","Eyeworth, Bedfordshire, England":"英国貝德福爾艾也沃斯","lifeSummary":"Lady Agnes Shaw于大约1425年出生在英国。她于1445年之前与Sir Henry Lockwood在英国结婚。他们至少是1个女儿的父母。"},"hr":{"about 1425–":"oko 1425.–preminula","1425–Male":"1425–preminuo","1445–1510":"1445–1510","1425–Female":"1425–preminula","1425":"1425","before 1445":"prije 1445.","1445":"1445","1455":"1455","1510":"1510","about 1425":"oko 1425.","about 1445":"oko 1445.","England":"England","Eyeworth, Bedfordshire, England":"Eyeworth, Bedfordshire, England"},"cs":{"about 1425–":"okolo 1425–Zesnulá","1425–Male":"1425–Zesnulý","1445–1510":"1445–1510","1425–Female":"1425–Zesnulá","1425":"1425","before 1445":"před 1445","1445":"1445","1455":"1455","1510":"1510","about 1425":"okolo 1425","about 1445":"okolo 1445","England":"Anglie","Eyeworth, Bedfordshire, England":"Eyeworth, Bedfordshire, Anglie"},"da":{"about 1425–":"omkring 1425–Afdød","1425–Male":"1425–Afdød","1445–1510":"1445–1510","1425–Female":"1425–Afdød","1425":"1425","before 1445":"før 1445","1445":"1445","1455":"1455","1510":"1510","about 1425":"omkring 1425","about 1445":"omkring 1445","England":"England","Eyeworth, Bedfordshire, England":"Eyeworth, Bedfordshire, England"},"nl":{"about 1425–":"circa 1425–Overleden","1425–Male":"1425–Overleden","1445–1510":"1445–1510","1425–Female":"1425–Overleden","1425":"1425","before 1445":"vóór 1445","1445":"1445","1455":"1455","1510":"1510","about 1425":"circa 1425","about 1445":"circa 1445","England":"England","Eyeworth, Bedfordshire, England":"Eyeworth, Bedfordshire, England"},"en":{"about 1425–":"about 1425–Deceased","1425–Male":"1425–Deceased","1445–1510":"1445–1510","1425–Female":"1425–Deceased","1425":"1425","before 1445":"before 1445","1445":"1445","1455":"1455","1510":"1510","about 1425":"about 1425","about 1445":"about 1445","England":"England","Eyeworth, Bedfordshire, England":"Eyeworth, Bedfordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Shaw","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lancashire): from Middle English <i>s(c)hawe</i>, <i>s(c)haghe</i> ‘small wood, grove, thicket’ (Old English <i>sceaga</i>). The surname may be topographic, for someone who lived in or by a small wood, or habitational, for someone from any of the many places so named. <i>Shaw</i> and <i>Shawe</i> are most frequent in Lancashire and Yorkshire, where Shaw in Oldham (Lancashire) may be a principal source of the surname. The English and Lowland Scottish surname was also established in Ireland in the 17th century.","Scottish: shortened form of various surnames from the Gaelic personal name <i>Sitheach</i>, derived from <i>sithech</i> ‘wolf’.","Irish (Down and Antrim): adopted for <b>Ó Síthigh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Sítheach</i>’, a personal name based on <i>sítheach</i> ‘peaceful’. Compare   Sheehy  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Show","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Cumberland): probably a variant of   Shaw  , perhaps representing a blend in Middle English of Old English <i>sceaga</i> and Old Norse <i>skógr</i>, both meaning ‘wood’.","Perhaps an Americanized form of German   Schau  ."]},{"name":"Sheehy","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Aileen, Aisling, Brigid, Declan, Egan, Eoin, Finbar, Ronan.","Irish (Limerick and Kerry): shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Síthigh</b>, ‘descendant of <i>Sítheach</i>’, or <b>Mac Síthigh</b> ‘son of <i>Sítheach</i>’, a form of the Irish personal name <i>Síodhach</i> ‘peaceful’, from the adjective <i>sítheach</i> ‘peaceful’ or ‘other worldly’ (see   Sheehan  ). The noun <i>síth</i>, from which this adjective derives, means basically ‘settlement’, hence both ‘peace’ and ‘place inhabited by other world beings’. This name was established in Ireland from the early 14th century, when a branch of the Scottish McDonnells, descended from <i>Sítheach</i>, great-grandson of Domhnaill, settled in the country."]}]},{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":30,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Agnes Shaw was born about 1425, in England. She married Sir Henry Lockwood before 1445, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1425–":"umbes 1425–Surnud","1425–Male":"1425–Surnud","1445–1510":"1445–1510","1425–Female":"1425–Surnud","1425":"1425","before 1445":"enn